Today they get my order wrong, and when calling the store I have never been so rudely spoken too when alerting them about the situation.  The employee even hung on me saying she was too busy.  I guess my $700 I've given them since moving here really isn't that important to them, so they are not important to me and I will never order from this Subway again. I should have read the reviews first. Clearly they have an issue with employees opening late and locking customers out early. I arrived on a Saturday night about 9:30pm. Sign on the door clearly says "open until 10", and a neon "OPEN" sign is blatantly lit up in the front window,  but the door is locked. There's even a person inside behind the counter in plain sight on her cell phone refusing to open the door, waving at us as if to indicate "yes, I'm here, I'm just not interested in working right now. Amazing typical Miami attention to service. At least the owners name & phone number are on the door. Called & left a message. Smart money bets they won't do anything about it though. Left a description of my visit along with photos and video on Subway's Facebook page and got a reply from ownership and corporate promising to do better. Hoping they will.

The location of this Subway restaurant is right next to two bus stops and a metromover or Miami mover stop. The approach to the subway should give you a pretty good idea of what to expect inside. The inside is just as shabby is the outside. People of questionable character hang around the store during the day. I shudder to think about the kinds of people that hang around once it's dark.  The inside of the store is filthy. The floor is dirty with streak marks all over it. Even though when I was there someone was cleaning the floor, it was clear to me that this place needs a deep rub down to get the grime out. The tables are unclean also.  The girls at work the counter are fine and made a reasonable sandwich but for some reason none of the ingredients felt fresh. It closer look at the lettuce showed me dark spots that arise when the lettuce has been sitting around for too long. Maybe they are you reusing lettuce between days and the same for other vegetables.  This is definitely not a place I would recommend unless you really have to go for some Subway.
